{
  "manifest_version": "0.4",
  "name": "safe-kaggle-mcp",
  "display_name": "Safe Kaggle MCP",
  "version": "0.4.2",
  "description": "Safety-first Kaggle MCP (41 tools): confirm-gated submit/delete, submission budget, prompt-injection fenced.",
  "long_description": "## Safe Kaggle MCP\n\nA **safety-first** MCP server connecting Claude to Kaggle — competitions, datasets, kernels (notebooks), models, and discussions. **41 tools.**\n\nUnlike other Kaggle MCP servers, every irreversible action is guarded:\n\n- **Two-call confirm tokens** for submit / delete / public-publish — an agent can't fire a destructive call in one shot.\n- **Per-competition submission budget** (default 5/day) surfaced in every response, so an iterating agent can't burn your daily quota.\n- **Private-by-default** creation; destructive/publish tools stay off behind env flags.\n- **Prompt-injection hardening** — all Kaggle-returned text (descriptions, forum posts, notebook source) is fenced as `<untrusted-content>`.\n- **Zip-slip-safe** sandboxed downloads; **credential redaction**; the API key never enters the model context.\n\n### Highlights other servers don't ship\n- `kaggle_competition_kickoff` — one call: metric + rules + data download + train/test EDA (auto-detects the target) + baseline plan.\n- `kaggle_eda_dataset` / `kaggle_eda_competition` — compact pandas digests (shape, dtypes, missingness, correlations), never raw rows.\n- `kaggle_competition_landscape` — deadline-sorted triage report.\n- `kaggle_leaderboard_track` — local snapshots with rank deltas (Kaggle has no historical API).\n- `kaggle_search_writeups` + `kaggle_search_discussions` — research winning solutions, every post untrusted-fenced.\n- `kaggle_audit_log` — a redacted ledger of every mutating action.\n\n### Setup\nInstall: `uvx --from safe-kaggle-mcp kaggle-mcp`. Provide a Kaggle token via `KAGGLE_API_TOKEN` (or `KAGGLE_USERNAME`/`KAGGLE_KEY`, or `~/.kaggle/`). Read-only tools work without credentials.\n\nSource & docs: https://github.com/parkseokjune/kaggle-mcp · also on PyPI (`safe-kaggle-mcp`) and the official MCP Registry (`io.github.parkseokjune/kaggle-mcp`).",
  "author": {
    "name": "parkseokjune",
    "url": "https://github.com/parkseokjune"
  },
  "homepage": "https://github.com/parkseokjune/kaggle-mcp",
  "documentation": "https://github.com/parkseokjune/kaggle-mcp#readme",
  "support": "https://github.com/parkseokjune/kaggle-mcp/issues",
  "license": "MIT",
  "keywords": [
    "kaggle",
    "mcp",
    "claude",
    "competitions",
    "datasets",
    "kernels",
    "models",
    "safety",
    "data-science"
  ],
  "server": {
    "type": "python",
    "entry_point": "kaggle_mcp.server",
    "mcp_config": {
      "command": "uvx",
      "args": [
        "--from",
        "safe-kaggle-mcp",
        "kaggle-mcp"
      ],
      "env": {
        "KAGGLE_USERNAME": "${user_config.kaggle_username}",
        "KAGGLE_KEY": "${user_config.kaggle_key}",
        "KAGGLE_API_TOKEN": "${user_config.kaggle_api_token}"
      }
    }
  },
